    "The Databricks model Dolly-v2-12B was trained on the Pythia-12B model using the Dolly dataset and demonstrates high-quality instruction-following behavior.",
    "We selected the modified Dolly dataset by Lee et al. (2024) that creates a high-quality preference dataset by comparing GPT-3.5-generated responses with human-crafted answers using GPT-4 judge.",
    "The final dataset 2 comprises 11.9K preference data where tied instances are excluded.",
    "10K training set was used for training and we sampled 300 pairs from the 1K test set for evaluation.",
    "In this section, we elaborate on details of experimental setups and results."
